De Lingua Latina, T. Scaurus’ De Orthographia and Festus’ De Verborum Significatione). The readings thus established are the basis for the ensuing linguistic analysis conducted on the fragments, in which new suggestions are proposed. In the hypothetical restoration of the text, a scheme of antiphonic recitation is reconstructed in which different ‘voices’ are identified. The review of the testimonies as a whole - together with a comprehensive collection of the classical sources on the Salian tradition - presents a picture of the linguistic and cultural frame in which the hymn was composed. By combining linguistic, philological and cultural data, this work offers a thorough survey of the Carmen Saliare to scholars interested in the most ancient phase of old Latin.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn Italian.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aLatin language, Preclassical to ca. 100 B.C. 0aLatin poetryxHistory and criticism. 0aSalii (Priests of Mars). 4aAltlatein. 4aCarmen saliare. 4aHymnologie. 4aLateinische Philologie. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh  aCarmen saliare.  aLatin philology.  ahymnology.  aold Latin.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2015 Part 1z978311076251808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070098508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2014z9783110369618oZDB-23-DGD08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Complete Package 2014z9783110369526oZDB-23-DGG0 cEPUBz97831104011100 cprintz978311040044140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311040104240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110401042423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110401042/original  a978-3-11-070098-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2015b2015  a978-3-1